        <h2>What was wrong with the original?</h2>
        <p>
            It was a good font, don't get me wrong! Some characters had some inconsistencies though, so I thought it'd be a reasonable project to work on, providing a great base to build upon. I also wanted to make a non-slanted version, so I discovered how to make a font variation — I learned lots!
        </p>
        <p>
            I still see some issues with this typeface (font metrics, using the <code>~</code> character as a ligature…), but sometimes you just need to let things go. Plus we've had no complaints so far, I guess people were just happy to be able to use a font like this!
        </p>
